oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mantel and fireplace in parlor of Cragfont
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Detail of mantel and fireplace in large parlor of Cragfont. The mantel has detailed woodwork and extends from the floor to the ceiling. The sill and apron are made of marble.

The late Georgian style home was built between 1798 and 1802, and was originally home of General James Winchester. It was named after the Rocky Bluff it is located on. Cragfont was occupied by the Winchester family until 1864.
